sentences: Tiara Nicole Thomas (born September 12, 1989) is an American singer-songwriter.
In 2013, Thomas was featured on the Wale single "Bad", which has been certified 3x Platinum by Recording Industry Association of America.
That same year, Thomas landed a label deal with Interscope Records, a label under the Interscope-Geffen-A&M group.
In 2021, she won the Grammy Award for Song of the Year for co-writing "I Can't Breathe".
In 2021, she won the Grammy Award for Song of the Year for co-writing "I Can't Breathe".
That same year, she received a Golden Globe nomination and won an Academy Award for Best Original Song, for co-writing the song "Fight for You", from Judas and the Black Messiah.
In June 2012, Thomas graduated from Ball State University.
Thomas met founders of The Board Administration Wale and Le'Greg O. Harrison in a club in Atlanta during a Wale concert in 2009.
After exchanging information and submitting music, she received a response and positive feedback after three months.
Thomas signed to The Board Administration in 2011.
On August 3, 2010, the world was introduced to Tiara Thomas on "The Cloud" with Wale through his mixtape More About Nothing.
Her name trended worldwide on May 30, 2011, on Twitter the day "The Cloud" video released.
Her name trended worldwide on May 30, 2011, on Twitter the day "The Cloud" video released.
Tiara Thomas was selected as a 2011–2012 Campaign Spokesperson for the American Eagle Outfitters Back to School We The People Campaign.
